# API Rules (Loaded for Route/API Files)

- ALL responses use the standard envelope: `{ success: boolean, data: T | null, error: { code: string, message: string, details: [] } | null, meta?: { page, limit, total } }`
- Route handlers are THIN: validate input, call service, format response. No business logic in routes.
- Validate request body/params/query with Zod (TS) or Pydantic (Python) at the route layer.
- Return appropriate HTTP status codes: 200 (success), 201 (created), 400 (bad input), 401 (unauthenticated), 403 (forbidden), 404 (not found), 422 (validation error), 500 (server error).
- Paginate all list endpoints. Default: page=1, limit=20, max=100.
- Include `Content-Type: application/json` header on all responses.
- Log all 4xx and 5xx responses with request context (method, path, user ID, duration).
- Never expose internal error details (stack traces, SQL errors) in production responses. Use generic error messages.
